               <msContents>
                  <summary>Declaration of property from Panopolis (modern name: Akhmim), Egypt, written on papyrus. Lists small holdings of sown land in various numbered plots in the Panopolite Nome. Part of the archive of Ammon, the well-known scholastikos, or lawyer</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Dimensions of fragments are 12.2 x 73.5 cm. or smaller</note>
                     <note type="general">7 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers on the recto</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 1.5 cm.; right margin of 2 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 182 R (a) was formerly P.Duk.inv. G 184 (a)</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
